    painPoint: "Ethan assumed he was UK non-resident because he was under 183 days. HMRC started a review in early 2026 citing the Statutory Residence Test sufficient ties — family, accommodation, 90-day tie, country tie = 4 UK ties = UK resident at 40 days.",
    discovery: "An HMRC review letter asking for evidence of UK residence status for 2024-25 prompted Ethan to look up the SRT for the first time.",
